✨HAPPY NEW YEAR!✨

Thinking back on all of 2022, I can’t help but think of how faithful our God is! My word for the year was “become” and while I don’t feel I’ve fully come into that word I feel I’ve taken small steps. So much I could say but I’ll just leave it I’m believing best days are ahead. 2023 is going to be filled with more memories to be made, more love to give out, and more laughter to be had. To say I’m thankful is an understatement. Let’s go 2023!🎉💐
Doesn’t get better than this💞🌸☀️

Happy Easter! Thank you Jesus for your sacrifice and the hope we have in You.

I can’t believe my little Charlotte turned TWO yesterday!! Where has the time gone?? She’s as spicy as she is sweet, she’s kind as she is strong, and she’s my girl! I love her so much! Happy birthday my girly girl!!!💞👑🌸🍉🎀🛍️🪩✨🩷
They were just too cute, these deserved a permanent place on my feed🇺🇸⭐️🇨🇱

🎉🎂🥳I can’t believe he’s F I V E!! I’m not emotional at allllll. 

It’s been the best five years of my life being this one’s mom. I wouldn’t trade any bit of it for the world. 

He’s an actual angel on earth and God gave him to us at the most perfect time. God has big big plans for this one — that’s for sure. Happy birthday Rhett Jones Hodges!!! I love you with all my heart!🫶🏼💙🩵

Between @pkgetaway, @growleader, and @motiongen I have so much hope for the world! Don’t care what the news says, there’s just so much hope. Hope for the world, hope for the church, and even hope for your own circumstance. I love @churchofthehighlands so much (like, literally we have the best team ever✌🏼) but also the big C church. And that’s what I love about all three of these events is churches from all over coming together as o n e. It’s like a glimpse of heaven!✨ sad + happy this week is over all at the same time. Only 360 more sleeps until next year!🎉 #Ilovemychurch #motion23

Transforming my entryway little by little. High end look on a budget!✨

Ever since moving in our house almost three years ago, I’ve developed a deep love for interiors. I think it’s taken me a long time to really pin down my style. I love mixing a traditional look with a modern twist while playing with some poppy colors. I wanted my entryway to have a little more color in it than the rest of my home because it sets the tone. If this room could talk, it would say, “I’m classy but I love a good time!” 🤣I wanted it be traditional yet fun.

I have been embracing taking my time with getting my home the way I want it. My home is hardly even how I want it but every good thing takes time😉 I’m the kind of person that would rather have it barely done so I can save my money on the things I really want, rather than just try to fill it up. I’m just now hanging things on the walls!🪞

I love a good hunt for good quality finds but on a budget. I found this mirror on #fbmp, found that lamp for $50 and put a new shade on it, and painted this @hobbylobby console that I‘ve had for 7 years ago (for $70!) and plus added new hardware! 

I’ve enjoyed so much making our house a home. I’ll show the “before the before” pictures in stories so you can really see how this space has been transformed!

Let me know your thoughts on this space in the comments and if you want to see more!👇🏼

#TogetherConf23 has officially wrapped and I’m so amazed at all God did!!💞💐🦋👚👑

Words can’t express my love for the church. I love the big C church, but also, I love my church. 

Staying planted in the church looks a whole lot like life — there are ups and downs, there’s hurt + pain, frustrations + tensions, there’s disagreements and a lot unmet expectations. And while those things may happen in the church, MY GOODNESS, there’s no where else I would rather be experiencing all the hard. 

Because, like my @bethallencunningham said, you may experience all those hard things in church, people also bless, they encourage, they heal, and they speak truth. In the house of God, there is joy and gladness, friendship, “togetherness”, restoration, and best of all, there’s JESUS.

Which is why, as long as it depends on me, I will be 🩷“devoted” to THE CHURCH the rest of my life. And I hope you will too because, after all, it’s the hope of the world.🕊️

Still can’t believe it!! What a FUN adventure! 🛞💰

We went to LA back in October but couldn’t say why we were there but we were actually there to film Wheel of Fortune! 

It was the longest day — Michael left at 6am that Thursday and there was still a chance he may not be selected to be on the show. He couldn’t have his phone all day so even after @kristinmartele and I arrived 11am, we still didn’t know if he even made it on the show! 

After sitting in the studio audience through filming for 5 hours, he finally came on! It was so much to take in and I remember thinking HOW IN THE WORLD DID HE SOLVE THOSE PUZZLES SO FAST! He does them pretty quick at home but it’s a whole other ballgame doing it in person! I was blown away!

All that to say, it was such a fun experience and I am SO PROUD of Michael but not in the slightest surprised. 

Thanks so much to everyone who watched and supported him! We are so thankful for all the love!!

#WOFMichael
